2026-04-16 12:15:10 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['PSU Output Cable (+) to Control Input Cable (+) connection', 'PSU Output Cable (−) to Control Input Cable (−) connection'] hypothesis_explanation='The measurement shows that the positive and negative lines from the power supply are crossed when connected to the control module: PSU (+) is currently connected to the control module’s 0 V line, and PSU (−) is connected to the control module’s 12 V line. This wiring inversion forward-biases the ‘switched cables’ red LED in the control module (explaining why it is on) and reverses the polarity seen by the load module’s diode, so no current can reach the lamps, which explains why the lamp never turns on. Correcting this by reconnecting PSU (+) to Control (+) and PSU (−) to Control (−) should restore normal operation and turn off the red LED while allowing the lamp to operate when the switch is closed.'
